# VDX File Format

VDX (Velt Document eXtension) is Velt's content file format that combines Markdown with V components.

## File Structure

A VDX file has two parts:

1. **Frontmatter** - TOML metadata between `+++` markers
2. **Content** - Markdown with embedded components

```markdown
+++
layout = "default"
title = "My Page"
+++

# Welcome

This is Markdown content.

<Callout type_="info">
This is a V component!
</Callout>
```

## Frontmatter

Frontmatter is written in TOML format:

```toml
+++
layout = "default"
title = "Page Title"
date = "2024-01-14"
author = "Your Name"
+++
```

### Available Fields

| Field | Required | Description |
|-------|----------|-------------|
| `layout` | ✅ | Layout template to use |
| `title` | ✅ | Page title (used in navigation) |
| `date` | ❌ | Publish date |
| `author` | ❌ | Author name |

## Markdown Support

VDX supports standard Markdown plus GFM (GitHub Flavored Markdown):

### Headers

```markdown
# H1
## H2
### H3
```

### Text Formatting

```markdown
**bold** and *italic*
`inline code`
[links](https://example.com)
```

### Code Blocks

````markdown
```typescript
const greeting = "Hello, World!";
console.log(greeting);
```
````

### Lists

```markdown
- Unordered item
- Another item

1. Ordered item
2. Another item
```

### Tables (GFM)

```markdown
| Header 1 | Header 2 |
|----------|----------|
| Cell 1   | Cell 2   |
```

## Embedding Components

Use JSX-like syntax to embed V components:

```markdown
<ComponentName prop="value" />

<ComponentName prop="value">
Child content here
</ComponentName>
```

### Self-Closing Tags

```markdown
<Hero title="Welcome" />
```

### With Children

```markdown
<Callout type_="warning">
**Warning:** This is important!
</Callout>
```

### Props

- Strings: `prop="value"`
- Expressions: `prop={expression}`
- Boolean: `enabled={true}`

## File Naming

### Standard Files

```
content/
├── index.vdx           → /index.html
├── docs.vdx            → /docs.html
└── guides/
    └── layouts.vdx     → /guides/layouts.html
```

### Localized Files

```
content/
├── docs.vdx            → /docs.html (English)
├── docs.ja.vdx         → /docs.ja.html (Japanese)
└── guides/
    ├── layouts.vdx     → /guides/layouts.html
    └── layouts.ja.vdx  → /guides/layouts.ja.html
```
